command.carpet.changePermanently.hover: Click to keep the settings in carpet.conf to save across restarts
carpet.rule.commandTick.description: Enables /tick command to analyze game speed for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandTickManipulate.descri: Allows the tick rate modifications of /tick for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandTickManipulate.extra: Values lower then commandTick have no effect
carpet.rule.commandPing.description: Enables /ping for players to get their ping for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandCarpetFill.descriptio: Enables /carpetfill command for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandCarpetFill.extra: This is a replica of the /fill command for fillUpdates and fillLimits
carpet.rule.commandCarpetClone.descripti: Enables /carpetclone command for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandCarpetClone.extra: This is a replica of the /clone command for fillUpdates and fillLimits
carpet.rule.commandCarpetSetBlock.descri: Enables /carpetsetblock command for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandCarpetSetBlock.extra: This is a replica of the /setblock command for fillUpdates and fillLimits
carpet.rule.commandPlayer.description: Enables /player command to control/spawn players for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandLog.description: Enables /log command to monitor events in the game via chat and overlays for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandSpawn.description: Enables /spawn command for spawn tracking for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandCameramode.descriptio: Enables /c and /s commands to quickly switch between camera and survival modes for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandMeasure.description: Enables /measure command for measuring distances for players with this permission level
carpet.rule.commandWaypoint.description: Enables /waypoint command for managing waypoints for players with this permission level and /tp [entities] waypoint (for permission level 2)
carpet.rule.fillUpdates.description: fill/clone/setblock and structure blocks cause block updates
carpet.rule.hopperCounters.description: Hoppers pointing to wool will count items passing through them
carpet.rule.hopperCounters.extra:
Enables /counter command, and actions while placing red and green carpets on wool blocks
Use /counter <color?> reset to reset the counter, and /counter <color?> to query
Counters are global and shared between players, 16 channels available
Items counted are destroyed, count up to one stack per tick per hopper
carpet.rule.tntPrimeMomentum.description: Removes random TNT momentum when primed and set to false
carpet.rule.tntHardcodeAngle.description: Sets the horizontal random angle on TNT for debugging of TNT contraptions
carpet.rule.silverFishDropGravel.descrip: Silverfish drop a gravel item when breaking out of a block
carpet.rule.shulkerSpawningInEndCities.d: Shulkers will respawn in end cities
carpet.rule.portalCreativeDelay.descript: Portals won't let a creative player go through instantly
carpet.rule.portalCreativeDelay.extra: Holding obsidian in either hand won't let you through at all
carpet.rule.fireChargeConvertsToNetherra: Fire charges from dispensers convert cobblestone to netherrack
carpet.rule.movableBlockEntities.descrip: Pistons can push block entities, like hoppers, chests etc.
carpet.rule.stackableShulkerBoxes.descri: Empty shulker boxes can stack to 64 when dropped on the ground
carpet.rule.stackableShulkerBoxes.extra: To move them around between inventories, use shift click to move entire stacks
carpet.rule.mobInFireConvertsSandToSouls: If a living entity dies on sand with fire on top the sand will convert into soul sand
carpet.rule.renewableSand.description: Cobblestone crushed by falling anvils makes sand
carpet.rule.doubleRetraction.extra: Gives pistons the ability to double retract without side effects.
carpet.rule.spawnChunkLevel.extra:
Like render distance (11 -> 23x23 actively loaded).
Be aware that a border of 11 chunks will stay loaded around that, once those chunks are loaded somehow.
Higher levels need lots of RAM (up to 7569 chunks loaded with level 32)
carpet.rule.renewableLava.description: Obsidian surrounded by 6 lava sources has a chance of converting to lava
carpet.rule.flippinCactus.description: Players can flip and rotate blocks when holding cactus
carpet.rule.flippinCactus.extra:
Doesn't cause block updates when rotated/flipped
Applies to pistons, observers, droppers, repeaters, stairs, glazed terracotta etc.
carpet.rule.renewableCoral.description: Coral structures will grow with bonemeal from coral plants
carpet.rule.optimizedFluidTicks.extra:
Testing showed around 2-3mspt improvement in regular worlds
Needs reloading of chunks to be effective
carpet.rule.dispensersTillSoil.descripti: Dispensers with hoes can till soil
carpet.rule.sleepingThresold.description: Percentage of sleeping players required to skip the night
carpet.rule.optimizedInventories.descrip: Optimizes hoppers and droppers interacting with chests ("Killer Hopper"s)
carpet.rule.optimizedInventories.extra: Tests showed ca. 5-10x performance improvement in worst-case scenarios
carpet.rule.movableBlockOverrides.descri: Override how pistons interact with any block. Adds weak stickyness behavior used by default for redstone components, flowerpots, etc.
carpet.rule.accurateBlockPlacement.descr: Allows client mods to specify the orientation of placed blocks
carpet.rule.dispensersBreakBlocks.descri: Gives dispensers the ability to break blocks using gunpowder
carpet.rule.netherMaps.description: Enables normal mapping of the nether
carpet.rule.netherMaps.extra: Useful for builds above the nether roof or SkyBlock
carpet.validator.tntAngle: Must be in the range [0,360) or -1 for default
counter.none: No items have been counted yet.
